            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "This feature is now officially supported! Displaying virtual text only in current line was implemented in https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/33517 and works for me on v0.11.1. 🥳 \n\n```lua\nvim.diagnostic.config{\n    virtual_text = { current_line = true, },  -- floating text only next to current line\n}\n```\n\nFYI, there's also a similar feature to put the diagnostics on lines below the current line.\n```lua\nvim.diagnostic.config{\n    virtual_lines = { current_line = true, },  -- floating text displayed on line below current line\n}\n```\n\nDon't set both to true or you'll see diagnostics in both places!",
